CONCURRENT-SESSIONS (PR-FLOW, S255 — main-authority is now branch protection, NOT the commit-lock):
  MAIN-AUTHORITY = GitHub branch protection (native, forge-enforced). The COMMIT-LOCK IS RETIRED
  (marker active-sessions/COMMIT-LOCK-RETIRED.md — no acquire/release/heartbeat/status). Serialization =
  PR merge-order (strict:true → the 2nd of two conflicting PRs rebases; the cloud `gate` full-suite is the
  write-skew backstop). The claims.md footprint-CAS is no longer load-bearing (history only).
  The BOARD (active-sessions/S<N>.md) is SUPERSEDED for authority but RETAINED for cross-machine VISIBILITY:
  boot step 0.5 still REGISTER your S<N>.md even solo (a solo session invisible to its own pre-wrap successor
  is still the S243 miss) + READ the board. A LIVE sibling => SUCCESSOR-mode: full session on NON-intersecting
  work; sibling open PRs / in-flight dispatches are CLAIMED not lost; only the WRAP defers. Boot authority
  check = `gh run list --branch main` + `gh pr list` (replaces `commit-lock.sh status`). Full instantiation:
  overlay {{concurrent_sessions_fills}}. Durable home: a flobase continuity module (scrml is the reference).

PROJECT-INTENT: scrml is "the future of how programming is done for the browser" (Rule 2) — a WHOLE-STACK
  compiler: the developer writes markup+logic+style+data in one .scrml; the compiler owns routing, server/
  client split (INFERRED, §12), fetch, serialization, reactivity, SQL (?{}), realtime (<channel>), auth
  (session + @currentUser + protect=), deploy (scrml build --target fly|railway|render|docker). NOT a view
  layer over a BaaS — scrml IS the backend. V1 = language-1.0 (freeze on high coverage). The mitosis (many
  smaller compiler/language PAs + a near-autonomous conformance-driven compiler build) is the near horizon.

